<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,266,812]" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,266,292]" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length of male 
<quantity box="[469,559,266,292]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="9" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
(approximate; forewings of 
<typeStatus box="[891,993,266,292]" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">holotype</typeStatus>
missing). Coloration and markings as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dietrich &amp; Dmitriev" authorityYear="2007" box="[181,339,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Neozygina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiapensis">
<emphasis box="[181,339,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">N. chiapensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[465,562,306,332]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="11.[151,255,1451,1475]" captionTargetBox="[245,1323,197,1410]" captionTargetId="figure-184@11.[244,1342,194,1427]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 3. New North American spp. of Neozygina, male pygofer (A, D, G, J, M, O, R, U, X), aedeagus in lateral (B, E, H, K, N, P, S, V, Y, AA) and posterior (C, F, I, L, Q, T, W, Z) views. A–C, N. antlera; D–F, N. chiapensis; G–I, N. hondurensis; J–L, N. mandibulata; M–N, N. obsoleta; O–Q, N. potosiensis; R–T, N. sonorensis; U–W, N. veracruzensis; X–Z, N. zapatai; AA, N. sordida." pageId="9" pageNumber="36">Fig. 3M</figureCitation>
) with dorsal appendage obsolete, reduced to heavily sclerotized ridge that extends half distance to apex; ventral appendage arising near apex, short, slender, extended posterad the abruptly bent dorsad; distal lobe narrow, weakly sclerotized dorsally. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1141,1238,386,412]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="11.[151,255,1451,1475]" captionTargetBox="[245,1323,197,1410]" captionTargetId="figure-184@11.[244,1342,194,1427]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 3. New North American spp. of Neozygina, male pygofer (A, D, G, J, M, O, R, U, X), aedeagus in lateral (B, E, H, K, N, P, S, V, Y, AA) and posterior (C, F, I, L, Q, T, W, Z) views. A–C, N. antlera; D–F, N. chiapensis; G–I, N. hondurensis; J–L, N. mandibulata; M–N, N. obsoleta; O–Q, N. potosiensis; R–T, N. sonorensis; U–W, N. veracruzensis; X–Z, N. zapatai; AA, N. sordida." pageId="9" pageNumber="36">Fig. 3N</figureCitation>
) with preatrium short; shaft in lateral view relatively broad and compressed basally with small dorsal teeth, gradually narrowed to midlength, distal half slender, tubular, strongly arcuate, with slender unpaired ventral preapical process; gonopore apical; apex with large unpaired distal spine extended ventrad.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
